cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.IT, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of removing rain streaks from images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves image processing techniques, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper uses morphological processing and PCA, which are common techniques in computer graphics and image processing, respectively, and could be classified under cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also involves the separation of image gradients, which could be related to information theory and signal processing, and hence could be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper uses sparsity priors, which is a common technique in machine learning, and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
